ro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*uBK8SuFGvMX7tNbs1dRy-w.jpeg)\\n\\nAfter clicking on Details button on Google Keep extension\\n\\n## **PocketðŸ“ƒ**\\n\\nTo save articles, videos and anything interesting over the Internet that you think is worth keeping in your stack. [Create an account](https://getpocket.com/signup?e=4) in Pocket.\\n\\nDownload the ***[Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ideashower.readitlater.pro&hl=en_IN&gl=US)***\\\\*\\\\*\\\\* or \\\\*\\\\*\\\\****[iOS](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pocket-save-read-grow/id309601447)***[ ](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pocket-save-read-grow/id309601447)app to read the saved articles anywhere on the go.\\n\\nJust set your tags and you are good to go now.\\n\\nNow, [add the Pocket extension](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/save-to-pocket/niloccemoadcdkdjlinkgdfekeahmflj?hl=en) to your browser and, done. Now, you are also ready to save your favorite articles from your computer and mobile phone and read anywhere anytime.\\n\\n## **DashlaneðŸ”**\\n\\nThere is a high probability that you might already be using a Password Manager. But, if you are not using one that I will recommend you to use one like Dashlane. There are other password managers as well like OnePassword, and all.\\n\\nBut, I personally prefer Dashlane as you can get the \\\\*\\\\*Premium for free for 6 monthsðŸ‘‰ \\\\*\\\\*[Make an account on Dashlane](https://www.dashlane.com/cs/BD9uWcvZtNjY)\\n\\nIt will auto-create, auto-save your passwords and also auto-fill your passwords, personal details like addresses, card details, and all.\\n\\n> If you cannot afford to pay for the service, you can use Bitwarden! An open-source password manager free-of-cost. [Download](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/bitwarden-free-password-m/nngceckbapebfimnlniiiahkandclblb?hl=en) Chrome extension.\\n\\n***[Follow me](https://medium.com/@akshitkumargautam)*** for more posts like this ahead and if you like this post, you can also support 